    "• Pooling functionMax pooling extracts the highest value inside each pooling window.",
    "• Fully connected layerThe input is flattened before the completely linked layer.• Generator Network G is the generating function, parameterized by θ g, and z is the random noise input.",
    "• Discriminator networkThe discriminator function, D, is parameterized by θ d, and the input, x, might be real or generated.",
    "It can turn a one-dimensional vector into a three-dimensional array(I * J)(i, j) = ∑ m ∑ n(i + m, j + n).K(m, n) ((I * K) + b) Output(i, j) = max m, n Input(2i + m, 2j + n) Output = Activation (Weight ⋅ Flatten (Input) + Bias) G(z; g) D(x, d).• Objective function GAN where; G stands for Generator, D stands for Discriminator, Pdata(x) = real-world data distribution, P(z) = generator distribution, x = Pdata sample (x),z = a sample taken from P (z), D(x) denotes a discriminator network, G(z) denotes the generator network.",
